x \in A \triangle B \;\equiv\; x \in A \not\equiv x \in B
 \begin{align} & x \in \overline{A \triangle B} \\ \equiv & \;\;\;\;\;\text{"definition of $\overline{\phantom\square}$; the above definition of $\triangle$"} \\ & \lnot(x \in A \:\not\equiv\: x \in B) \\ \equiv & \;\;\;\;\;\text{"logic: simplify"} \\ & x \in A \:\equiv\: x \in B \\ \Leftarrow & \;\;\;\;\;\text{"logic: weakening -- suggested by the shape of the left hand side ($A \cap B$)"} \\ & x \in A \:\land\: x \in B \\ \equiv & \;\;\;\;\;\text{"definition of $\cap$"} \\ & x \in A \cap B \\ \end{align} 
